      • setCurrentOperands

        public void setCurrentOperands(int value)
        Description copied from class: Operator
        Sets the number of operands currently used

        This is the number of operands this instance is using. For example, if 1 it indicates that this is a unary operator
        The number of operands must be between a minimun and a maximum which is set with setOperandsLimit

        Overrides:
        setCurrentOperands in class Operator
        Parameters:
        value - A number indicating how many operands this operator needs

        Description copied from class: Operator
        Executes the operation performed by the operator

        Every concrete implementation of Operator must implement this method with the operation that it has to do.

        Specified by:
        executeOperation in class Operator
        Parameters:
        operands - A stack containing the operands in reversed order
        memory - A reference to the main math memory
        Returns:

        Throws:
        ExpressionException - The exception is thrown when there is an evaluation problem
